	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001302_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">Steamer Pearl 3<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi> April </p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858 </p>
<lb/><p>Sir </p>
<lb/><p>As another sextant 
<lb/>is required for the use 
<lb/>of the <placeName>Zambesi</placeName>
<lb/>Expedition in addition 
<lb/>to that we already possess 
<lb/>I beg leave to apply 
<lb/>to you for one, and 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001302_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>I will account for 
<lb/>it to the Admiralty<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Skead R.N. </persName></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001302_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/><p><handShift new="#other"/> Lamb Collection 
<lb/>392(19) </p>
<lb/><p>The annexed letter I received 
<lb/>from the personal friend of 
<lb/>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Livingstone - <persName>Captain Skead</persName>, late 
<lb/>R.N. and Admiralty Surveyor 
<lb/>to the Zambesi expedition - and 
<lb/>I can therefore testify to its 
<lb/>genuineness. 
<lb/>N. L. Spindle 
<lb/><hi rend="underline">30/8/74</hi></p>
			
</div>
